The paper discusses motion planning for self-driving vehicles, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) category. The use of a jointly learnable behavior and trajectory planner involves machine learning techniques, which could place it under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also mentions the use of perception and prediction, which could relate to computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the focus on safety and obeying traffic rules suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY).
